trans-unit.source: Gets the name of the protection algorithm. If none was set then the keystore provider will use its default protection algorithm. The name of the default protection algorithm for a given keystore type is set using the 'keystore.<type>.keyProtectionAlgorithm' security property. For example, the keystore.PKCS12.keyProtectionAlgorithm property stores the name of the default key protection algorithm used for PKCS12 keystores. If the security property is not set, an implementation-specific algorithm will be used.

trans-unit.source: HTML provides a well known set of features without exactly specifying the display characteristics. Swing has a theme mechanism for its look-and-feel implementations. trans-unit.source: HTML.Attributes defines a type safe enumeration of html attributes. If an attribute key of a tag is defined in HTML.Attribute, the HTML.Attribute will be used as the key, otherwise a String will be used. For example <p foo=bar class=neat> has two attributes. foo is not defined in HTML.Attribute, where as class is, therefore the AttributeSet will have two values in it, HTML.Attribute.CLASS with a String value of 'neat' and the String key 'foo' with a String value of 'bar'.
trans-unit.target: HTML.Attributes는 html 속성의 형식 안전 열거를 정의합니다. 태그의 속성 키가 HTML.Attribute에 정의되어 있으면 HTML.Attribute가 키로 사용되고, 그렇지 않으면 문자열이 사용됩니다. 예를 들어 <p foo = bar class = neat>에는 두 가지 속성이 있습니다. foo는 HTML.Attribute에 정의되어 있지 않으므로 AttributeSet에는 String 값이 'neat'인 HTML.Attribute.CLASS와 String 값이 'foo'인 문자열 키 'foo'가 있습니다. 바'.
